cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it focuses on the analysis of conversational talk and its implications for computational models. It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with the audio aspect of multi-party interaction. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as it discusses the design of "smart" multi-party applications. The paper also touches upon the use of AI in modeling multi-party interaction, which could place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the study of sociable talk and its organization within small groups could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
